  "commit_message": "feat(eslint-plugin): harden-exports skips M.* pattern makers (#2632)\n\nTwo complementary `@endo/eslint-plugin` changes around Pattern makers.\n\nThe existing `harden-exports` rule no longer demands `harden(name)` on\nan export whose declarator is initialized to a Pattern maker call\n(`M.something(...)`). Pattern makers already return hardened values, so\nthe follow-up `harden()` is redundant noise. The check matches\nconservatively: only when the callee's immediate object identifier is\nthe literal name",
